      <hedline>
        <hl1>NESTLE'S PROFIT SOARS</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Andrew Ross Sorkin</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Sorkin, Andrew Ross</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Nestle SA posts better-than-expected earnings for first half of year; net profit rose 35 percent, to 2.8 billion Swiss francs, or $1.61 billion, from 2.08 billion francs in year-earlier period (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The world's largest food company, Nestle, posted better-than-expected earnings for the first half of the year, buoyed by increased sales in Asia, Africa, Eastern Europe and Latin America. The Swiss company said first-half net profit jumped 35 percent, to 2.8 billion Swiss francs, or $1.61 billion, from 2.08 billion francs in the period a year earlier.</p>
        <p>Andrew Ross Sorkin</p>
      </block>
